article.description: — Daryl Banks III posted 13 points as St. Peter's rolled past Manhattan 73-51 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Banks leads St. Peter's over Manhattan 73-51
article.linkText: Banks leads St. Peter's over Manhattan 73-51
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Daryl Banks III posted 13 points as St. Peter's rolled past Manhattan 73-51 on Tuesday night. Doug Edert, KC Ndefo and Fousseyni Drame each added 12 points for St. Peter's (15-11, 13-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Warren Williams had 12 points for the Jaspers (14-14, 7-12). Josh Roberts added eight rebounds. The Peacocks improve to 2-0 against the Jaspers this season. St. Peter's defeated Manhattan 77-51 on Jan. 28. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
